The paper discusses a planning framework for robotics, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. The use of Hierarchical Task Network (HTN) planning and the focus on agent-based task planning also suggests that it could belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Multi-Agent Systems (cs.MA) sub-categories. The mention of social rules and behavior also suggests that it could belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category. Finally, the use of geometric reasoning and validation suggests that it could belong to the Learning (cs.LG) sub-category.
